    <div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='7505#1257974300'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2009-11-11T21:18:20+00:00">Nov 11, 2009 09:18 PM UTC</time> by <b>Neha Sharma</b><a class="anchor" name="1257974300">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>**An update was made to this Ticket based on an update made to dynamically-linked Ticket #7574 in Project Open Science Grid**

Hi Neha,

Thanks for the ping!  We&#39;re running ok, so I applied the SQL.  I&#39;m also
running a script to add the sticky flag to all the files that don&#39;t have
it.</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='7505#1256152987'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2009-10-21T19:23:07+00:00">Oct 21, 2009 07:23 PM UTC</time> by <b>Neha Sharma</b><a class="anchor" name="1256152987">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>**An update was made to this Ticket based on an update made to dynamically-linked Ticket #7574 in Project Open Science Grid**

[saewill@.... - Wed Oct 21 19&#58;28&#58;06 2009]&#58;

Great, it&#39;s good to  have an explanation!! Only one of our
reservations
are configured this way, so that explains why it doesn&#39;t affect all
files.  Do you have advice on how to get to a good config?  I don&#39;t
see
an command in the admin console to change the accessLatency.  (Maybe
there&#39;s a way to change it in the db?).  We have many thousand files
in
this reservation.  If we have to delete and recreate the reservation,
do
we need to delete and re-download those files as well, or can we
migrate
them to the new reservation?

Sarah,

I am sorry no such command. So need to run some SQL

1) Check that the linkgroup that spacereservation belongs to allows online&#58;

select onlineallowed from srmlinkgroup where id in (select linkgroupid from srmspace where id=?);

substitute ? with id of space reservation you are talking about if query return 1 you are OK if not,
modify it&#58;

update linkgroup set onlineallowed=1 where id in (select linkgroupid from srmspace where id=?);

2) modify space reservation&#58;

update srmspace set accesslatency=(select id from srmaccesslatency where name=&#39;ONLINE&#39;) where id=?&#39;

<div id='show_1088178975' class=''><button class="btn">Show More</button></div><div class='detail hidden' id='detail_1088178975'>replace ? with id of space reservation in question.

I will make admin command to allow this in the future.
