On Sep 21, 2009, at 1&#58;57 PM, Sarah Williams wrote&#58;

-----BEGIN PGP SIGNED MESSAGE-----
Hash&#58; SHA1

Hi dCache Users &amp; OSG storage forum,

On Sep 18, we had a large number of files go missing on disk (resulting
in pnfs ghosts) on one particular pool. In the log I see&#58;

18 Sep 2009 12&#58;11&#58;41 (uct2-s2_6) [] trying to remove
000600000000000001B36AA0

What does that message mean? There&#39;s no other information in the log
about why the files are gone.

I note disk usage on this pool is high (99%).  However, these are old
files, not recently written.

- --Sarah</pre></div><legend>Similar Recent Tickets <small>modified within the last 30 days</small></legend><div id="similar_tickets"><p class="muted">No similar tickets found.</p></div>
